We never believed that a political system is based solely on votes. At any and every point of our knowing of people, places, and things, there is a chance there for politics-making. We all have opinions on what makes things work for ourselves, our families, our neighborhoods, our towns, our country, because we are faced with them. No matter how trivial these opinions seem, they can be the most vivid, effective, and powerful political thoughts. Open Congress breaks into the arcane, unengaging system of Congress and its bills because getting at what bills are, what they propose to do, how they can be effective, who is behind each bill, where the money is coming from, and why the bill exists in the first place, is just the beginning of turning your societal and political needs and ideas into a real thing of our culture and country. Your ideas and thoughts are important to making our political system something that is not just about votes.
</p>
